As AI continues to become more advanced and autonomous, however, it is critical to ensure its safe, fair, and ethical development and use.There are many open questions around how to ensure the responsible development of AI. How do we properly safeguard people's privacy and security as AI systems gain more autonomy and access to data? How do we make sure the economic benefits of AI are broadly shared across society? How do we align AI systems' goals with human values and priorities? How do we establish appropriate oversight and governance mechanisms to manage AI risks that we have not yet anticipated?Addressing these complex questions will require proactive leadership from researchers, companies, governments, and civil society.
